  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n+ Finish initial sync\r\n+ Finish regular sync\r\n+ Some gossip blocks came and be validated  successfully, the latest one is \r\n\r\n```2020-07-31 13:49:05  [GOSSIP]        verbose: Incoming block at slot: 228695\r\n2020-07-31 13:49:05  [CHAIN]            info: Processed new chain head newChainHeadRoot=0x6a767222984c5214c625ddb9c3984fca957991bc76b41db34e79aef8f0fa97b7, slot=228695, epoch=7146\r\n```\r\n+ Next block comes but it's not the head\r\n```\r\n2020-07-31 13:49:17  [GOSSIP]        verbose: Incoming block at slot: 228696\r\n```\r\n+ We can receive some more gossip blocks but after a while we cannot do that anymore because the epoch of head is too different from the incoming block\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n+ I notice that we receive enough gossip blocks one after another but we always validate it based on our head which maybe too far from that block\r\n+ So we should try to get epochContext of parent block first, if we don't have then we get epochContext of head\r\n",
